    "Thus, the test performance difference between M D1 and M D2 is mostly attributed to the second type of questions: ones that are known to M, i.e.",
    "M can answer them correctly since it posses the relevant knowledge.",
    "Thus, M D1 and M D2 must rely on their pre-existing knowledge to answer such questions, and a lower performance on such question can be only categorized as an hallucination w.r.t.",
    "pre-existing knowledge.",
    "This section expands §3 with additional details about our P Correct approximation."
  ],
